## Quality bar — self-check before delivering

- [ ] No more than 5 items in "Top of mind."
- [ ] Every "Top of mind" item has a deadline and a suggested action.
- [ ] Compliance and KPI sections are present (even if "none this cycle").
- [ ] Calendar table covers the right window for the cadence.
- [ ] At least one specific "cut" recommendation in "What you can cut today" (unless calendar is genuinely light).
- [ ] No labeled/Confidential content pasted into the digest body — summarized and linked instead.
- [ ] If run unattended, no approval-gated actions taken; queued for {{ persona.first_name }} instead.
- [ ] No item assumes {{ persona.first_name }} will do the work himself if a direct report or partner-org owner is appropriate.

If any check fails, revise before delivering.

## Privacy and boundaries

- Reading Confidential or labeled mail/docs elevates the session's sensitivity level — never write that content to the plain-text digest or a Teams channel. Summarize and link.
- Never include the full body of confidential emails in the digest — link to the thread and summarize.
- For compliance-flagged items, do not paste regulator names, case numbers, or audit findings into the digest body. Use "compliance item — see link" and protect the underlying source.
- Never auto-decline or auto-reply without explicit approval. Recommend only.
